result.execSummary:
The defendant Jared S. Hancock was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 4:17 p.m. Defendant Jared S. Hancock in court.  Calling 15ct92 and 15cm521. Defendant states currently searching for employment - trying to establish residency in Mole Lake - defendant requests community service. Court authorizes community service at $10/hr. Court tells defendant he needs to perform substantial amount of community service or pay substantial amount prior to next hearing. Adj. 4:20 p.m.  Review hearing scheduled for July 18, 2016 at 03:00 pm.
Copy of JOC sent to defendant

3:08 p.m. Defendant Jared S. Hancock in court.  Michael William Schiek appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant wishes to proceed on own - Waiver free and voluntary - Defendant enters guilty plea - requests matter be dismissed since he has worked things out and has been in jail for 11 days - Schiek statement to potential resolution - Defendant enters guilty plea -   Court reads on waiver of rights and tendering plea. Waiver free and voluntary. Court finds that a factual basis for the plea exists and finds defendant guilty. Schiek/Defendant statement to sentencing - Court imposes court costs of $443. Appeal rights given. Payment plan application given. Adj. 3:20  Review hearing scheduled for April 25, 2016 at 03:00 pm.

1:54 p.m. Defendant Jared S. Hancock in court, via video, in custody.  Michael William Schiek appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  In receipt of complaint, right to counsel - Schiek statement to bail - Court sets $ sig bond. Adj. 1:56 p.m.  Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for January 25, 2016 at 02:30 pm.
